5000|$|Maximum {{aperture}} {{also affects}} {{the shape of}} a <b>lens</b> <b>hood.</b> As the aperture gets larger the amount of light and consequentially the amount of the frame the sensor [...] "sees" [...] increases. This can be seen when comparing two <b>lens</b> <b>hoods</b> of the same focal length but with differing apertures - compare the <b>lens</b> <b>hood</b> of a telephoto 4 lens with that of the same lens but with a maximum aperture of 2.8.|$|R
