50|$|In photography, a <b>lens</b> <b>hood</b> or <b>lens</b> shade is {{a device}} {{used on the}} front end of a lens to block the Sun or other light source(s) to prevent glare and <b>lens</b> flare. Lens <b>hoods</b> may also be used to protect the lens from {{scratches}} and the elements without having to put on a lens cover.The geometry of a <b>lens</b> <b>hood</b> is dependent on three things: the focal length of the lens, the size of the front lens element and the dimensions of the image sensor or film in the camera.|$|R
